anna marie smith occasion interdisciplinary studies in the humanities home home issues rss admin login anna marie smith home anna marie smith professor of government at cornell university is a political theorist with research interests in the fields of jurisprudence and normative political theory distributive justice and socioeconomic rights public policy education and poverty assistance feminist theory and feminist legal studies critical race theory and the rhetoric of modern state power and citizenship her most recent book is welfare reform and sexual regulation 2007 she held a mellon new directions fellowship at columbia law school in 2008 9 and she was a member of the institute for advanced study in 2009 10 articles by author neo eugenics a feminist critique of agamben volume 2 recent issues volume 2 12.20 2010 volume 1 10.15 2009 arcade
